The wife of a sheriff deputy has given graphic testimony alleging he tortured and sexually assaulted her and her new partner in a vicious two-hour attack.

The woman was married to defendant Robert McClain, a former Los Angeles County sheriff's deputy, and pretended to castrate her 23-year-old boyfriend as the husband watched, prosecutors previously said.

As she took to the stand, the unidentified woman was visibly distressed as she told jurors McClain, 38, from Irvine, California, slashed her boyfriend repeatedly, beating him to the point of brain damage.

